T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1073
EP  - 1102
VL  - 75
IS  - 4
KW  - Assortative matching
KW  - nontransferable utility
KW  - risk sharing
KW  - intrahousehold allocation
KW  - principal-agent
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2007.00782.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We present sufficient conditions for monotone matching in environments where utility is not fully transferable between partners. These conditions involve not only complementarity in types of the total payoff to a match, as in the transferable utility case, but also monotonicity in type of the degree of transferability between partners. We apply our conditions to study some models of risk sharing and incentive problems, deriving new results for predicted matching patterns in those contexts.
ER  - 

