JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1191
EP  - 1208
VL  - 75
IS  - 4
KW  - Statistical inverse
KW  - endogenous variable
KW  - instrumental variable
KW  - optimal rate
KW  - nonlinear integral equation
KW  - nonparametric regression
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2007.00786.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We consider nonparametric estimation of a regression function that is identified by requiring a specified quantile of the regression ?error? conditional on an instrumental variable to be zero. The resulting estimating equation is a nonlinear integral equation of the first kind, which generates an ill-posed inverse problem. The integral operator and distribution of the instrumental variable are unknown and must be estimated nonparametrically. We show that the estimator is mean-square consistent, derive its rate of convergence in probability, and give conditions under which this rate is optimal in a minimax sense. The results of Monte Carlo experiments show that the estimator behaves well in finite samples.
ER  - 

